-- Merrill falls 3.2 percent as analyst sees write-down
-- 
-- Fri Jun 27, 2008 9:45am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/06/27/us-markets-stocks-beforethebell-idUSN2736697120080627

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Shares of Merrill Lynch & Co Inc MER.N fell 3.2 percent to $32.00 on Friday before the opening bell as a Lehman Brothers analyst forecast Merrill Lynch will likely incur $5.4 billion of write-downs in the second quarter. 

 (Reporting by  Walker Simon ; Editing by Theodore d'Afflisio)